      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAYEKI (7) ran a much improved race last time, charging home to finish a close-up fourth after being slow to begin at the start. Fitter again and looks suited by the extra ground. Gets chance. SNOBBERY (5) also ran a much better race last time at just his second outing, working home well to finish third over 1600m at this track. Finds a suitable race and can build on that solid recent effort. ALWAYS SHINING (1) is a nine-start maiden who could only manage to finish fifth at his latest appearance over 1600m at Moe after he was well back on straightening. Solid top-three chance on his best figures. DOWNTHERABBITHOLE (6) finished 11 lengths away in tenth at her last appearance over 1887m at Kyneton on February 27. Better than that and worth keeping safe.  DELPHIAN (2) is fitter for two runs in and can improve sharply.",
